# Primary app: Expo (React Native). Copy to mobile/.env — or use repo root .env / .env.local
# (app.config.js maps NEXT_PUBLIC_* → EXPO_PUBLIC_* when Expo vars are unset).
#
# --- Supabase Dashboard (manual) — if confirmation emails never arrive ---
# 1) Authentication → Logs: look for SMTP / rate-limit errors.
# 2) Authentication → SMTP: enable Custom SMTP for production (built-in mail is rate-limited).
#    Example (SendGrid): Host smtp.sendgrid.net, Port 587, User "apikey", Pass = API key,
#    Sender = verified sender (e.g. noreply@yourdomain.com).
# 3) Authentication → URL configuration:
#    - Site URL: dev e.g. exp:// or your Expo dev client; prod = https://your-app.com
#    - Redirect URLs: must include EXPO_PUBLIC_AUTH_REDIRECT_URL below AND Expo deep links from Linking.createURL (see README).
# 4) Authentication → Email templates → send a test email from the Dashboard.
# 5) Dev only: you may turn OFF "Confirm email" under Providers → Email to skip inbox (not for production).
#
# Note: @supabase/auth-ui-react-native is not published on npm; this app uses custom screens + AuthContext.

# Supabase — anon JWT (eyJ…) or publishable key (sb_publishable_…) from Dashboard → API
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJ...
# Optional alias (same as ANON_KEY for templates that use EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_KEY)
# EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_KEY=sb_publishable_...

# Deployed Next.js API (no trailing slash) — mood/tasks/bootstrap when using real auth
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://your-app.vercel.app

# Email confirmation redirect (must be listed in Supabase Auth → Redirect URLs). Use your deployed Next.js origin + /auth/callback, e.g. https://your-app.vercel.app/auth/callback — if unset, Expo Linking generates a dev URL (add that to Supabase too).
# EXPO_PUBLIC_AUTH_REDIRECT_URL=https://your-app.vercel.app/auth/callback

# ElevenLabs TTS for task voice guidance (server needs ELEVENLABS_API_KEY — see root .env.example)
# EXPO_PUBLIC_USE_ELEVENLABS_TTS=true
#
# Optional dev-only: direct client calls (key is bundled — rotate if leaked). Prefer deployed Next + proxy.
# EXPO_PUBLIC_ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=
# EXPO_PUBLIC_ELEVENLABS_VOICE_ID=

# Mock auth (no Supabase round-trip). Seed profile: mobile/contexts/AuthContext.tsx → MOCK_USER
# EXPO_PUBLIC_USE_MOCK_AUTH=true

# Optional: require fixed email+password in mock mode (set both)
# EXPO_PUBLIC_MOCK_DEV_EMAIL=demo@wellness.app
# EXPO_PUBLIC_MOCK_DEV_PASSWORD=local-dev-password

# Dev bypass button (__DEV__ only): sign in with a seeded Supabase user (skip email issues). Create this user in Dashboard → Auth → Users, or use mock auth without Supabase.
# EXPO_PUBLIC_DEV_BYPASS_EMAIL=dev@wellness.test
# EXPO_PUBLIC_DEV_BYPASS_PASSWORD=WellnessDev123!

# Pro: bonus strip on task completion (mirrors root NEXT_PUBLIC_WELLNESS_PRO via app.config.js)
# EXPO_PUBLIC_WELLNESS_PRO=true

# After env changes: cd mobile && npx expo start -c
